note.p:
Pub. L. 118–31, div. F, title LXVII, § 6707(a)(1), Dec. 22, 2023, 137 Stat. 1017, provided that: “(a) Country Reports on Human Rights Practices.—“(1) In general.—The Secretary [of State] shall examine the production of the 2023 and subsequent annual Country Reports on Human Rights Practices by the Assistant Secretary for Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor as required under sections 116(d) and 502B(b) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 (22 U.S.C. 2151n(d), 2304(b)) to maximize—“(A) cost and personnel efficiencies;
“(B) the potential use of data and analytic tools and visualization; and
“(C) advancement of the modernization agenda for the Department [of State] announced by the Secretary on October 27, 2021.”
